This dark brown sign is eaten through with salt rot. There are darker deep creases etched out as reading "Harbor Master".
One leg seems slightly loose. You wonder how long the stool will last.

Month of Stars day 14
A nasty storm is brewin today. I must remember ta warn the Sanitary Department that an excess of debris will be washin up on shore.

Damn them fool Elves! Do they really think that I will ever let them dock in me harbor? Not after the way they have treated me an my kin. Not after Rock Helm.

Oh yeah, that fella Ratcliff from the temple has become me second 'ere.


Month of Stars day 20
Blast it all! I almost let two ships smack each other head on today as I was flaggin them in. My 'ead hurts and I 'aven't gotten a good nights sleep in almost a week. Dang blasted bad dreams.

Month of Sails day 10
Heavy fog today. I coulda sworn I heard cries for help from Devils Reef. I sent Ratcliff rowing out there ta check on it, but he all he saw was a bit o'gurgling bubbles off shore an nothin else.

Month of Sails day 11
That Swan fella stopped by to try an get me ta allow his pixie friends to come ashore. I told him if they don't want to be bouncing off the reef all day then they best be goin home!

Takin the rest o'the day off. Gotta try an get some sleep without them blasted night terrors. The nightmare be getting more specific now. I keep seein some twisted landscape with octopuses in the desert. If I dun get some rest soon I'm gonna kill someone! Hopefully it'll be one o'them dang pixie folk.

Month of Wind day 22
That pansy Ratcliff quit on me today. He said that I've tried to strangle 'im for the last time. When did he grow a spine? Nothin but a pathetic mass of waste, that's what he is.

Month of Wind day 23
I feel bad 'bout what I wrote yesterday. I canna even figure out when I started having urges ta strangle people and stick 'em in a sack. I better stop writin this stuff down, afore it gits me in trouble or something...

This bulletin board is covered with notes of all kind. The pleas for help and sketches of missing loved drawn upon these notes serve as a memorial to a time before the repopulation of Tobaro. The faces and messages tug at your heart as you scan over the scraps of paper. Amidst the messages you can find a few newer bits of communication as the villagers try to get over the horrors of the past.
This stone idol is covered with mysterious runes and depicts an early picture of a man kissing the inside of a woman's wrist.

This simple and weathered sign denotes a stop on the Duke's Caravan Routes

Caravans
*     *     *     *     *     *
Caravans can be led between the towns of Brosna, Benzor, Sholo, and Tobaro. To start the processes speak with a Caravan Master. Follow the dialog, choose a destination and ask to lead the caravan. You will now be followed by a caravan creature. This creature must survive to the destination in order to get your reward. Rewards differ depending on the distance and danger between routes. You can only lead one caravan between any rout at any one time however you may lead multiple caravans for different routes at the same time. For example: you can only take one Caravan Creature from Benzor to Brosna but on your way there you can pick up another Caravan Creature in Sholo and deliver them both to Brosna. If you wish your Caravan Creature to stop while you scout ahead simple speak to them and work through the dialog. NOTE: You may not travel by sea or use teleportation magic including the Pendent of Golden Wings while leading a caravan. First you must release the creature or log out and then back in. But know if you do crash or log out your Caravan Creature will be abandoned. Attacking a Caravan Creature including the use of AOE spells will be seen as a hostile act and will have repercussions.
